race.comment: Former NSW galloper YOROKOBI (7) has hit the frame in all three runs since joining the new stable and this is not an overly strong affair. Drops back a furlong from the latest outing and should be hitting the line with gusto. MARCH MADNESS (2) has gotten better with each run this time in and looks to be working up to that elusive maiden victory. Include in calculations. COLONEL PARKER (1) has placed one from one around this circuit and is a must for the multiples. NATIONAL GOAL (4) rounds out the selection having finished second at this course and distance two starts ago. Race depth falls away quickly thereafter.
